The invention will below be described in connection to a number of drawings, in which:
Figure 1 schematically shows an engine with a turbocharger system according to the invention;
Figure 2 shows a diagram over different tank volumes, tank pressure, pipe diameters and delta pressure during a predetermined time period;
Figure 3 shows a diagram over of an example of predetermined scenarios, and in which;
Figure 4 schematically shows a flow chart on a method for controlling a turbocharger system 1 according to figures 1-3.

claim.claim-text:
A turbocharger system (1) according to claim 5 or 6, wherein the predetermined scenarios of estimated engine load comprising:
- the estimated desired change in engine load going from no or low load to medium high load, wherein the first control unit (1 a) is arranged to control the tank (3) to push a first subset of the compressed gas into the manifold conduit (4), wherein the first subset corresponds to the predetermined pulse of compressed air being discharged giving the estimated desired turbocharger effect and/or;
- the estimated desired change in engine load going from no or low load to high load, wherein the first control unit (1 a) is arranged to control the tank (3) to push a second subset of the compressed gas into the manifold conduit (4), wherein the second subset corresponds to the predetermined pulse of compressed air being discharged giving the estimated desired turbocharger effect and/or;
- the estimated desired change in engine load going from medium high to high load, wherein the first control unit (1a) is arranged to control the tank (3) to push a third subset of the compressed gas into the manifold conduit (4), wherein the third subset corresponds to the predetermined pulse of compressed air being discharged giving the estimated desired turbocharger effect and/or;
- the estimated desired change in engine load going from any value below a predetermined threshold value to or above the threshold value, the threshold value being set as a value below a maximum value of engine load or to the maximum value of the engine load, wherein the first control unit (1 a) is arranged to control the tank (3) to push a fourth subset of the compressed gas into the manifold conduit (4), wherein the fourth subset corresponds to the predetermined pulse of compressed air being discharged giving the estimated desired turbocharger effect.
